Use the standard library
This is how to valid_date of date:
   Remember that length is date's length
   Remember that result is 0
   When length is not 10, then:
      The answer is result
   End when
   Remember that month_str is []
   Remember that day_str is []
   Remember that year_str is []
   When length is 10, then:
      Add month_str to item 0 in date
      Add month_str to item 1 in date
      Add day_str to item 3 in date
      Add day_str to item 4 in date
      Add year_str to item 6 in date
      Add year_str to item 7 in date
      Add year_str to item 8 in date
      Add year_str to item 9 in date
   End when
   Remember that month is sum of (product of 10 and (diff of item 0 in month_str and 48)) and (diff of item 1 in month_str and 48)
   Remember that day is sum of (product of 10 and (diff of item 0 in day_str and 48)) and (diff of item 1 in day_str and 48)
   Remember that valid is 1
   When month is less than 1, then:
      Remember that valid is 0
   End when
   When month is more than 12, then:
      Remember that valid is 0
   End when
   When day is less than 1, then:
      Remember that valid is 0
   End when
   When valid is 1, then:
      Remember that is_31_day_month is 0
      When month is 1, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 3, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 5, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 7, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 8, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 10, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 12, then:
         Remember that is_31_day_month is 1
      End when
      Remember that is_30_day_month is 0
      When month is 4, then:
         Remember that is_30_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 6, then:
         Remember that is_30_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 9, then:
         Remember that is_30_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 11, then:
         Remember that is_30_day_month is 1
      End when
      When month is 2, then:
         When day is more than 29, then:
            Remember that valid is 0
         End when
      End when
      When is_31_day_month is 1, then:
         When day is more than 31, then:
            Remember that valid is 0
         End when
      End when
      When is_30_day_month is 1, then:
         When day is more than 30, then:
            Remember that valid is 0
         End when
      End when
   End when
   Remember that result is valid
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> valid_date of [48, 51, 45, 49, 49, 45, 50, 48, 48, 48] 
1
>>> valid_date of [49, 53, 45, 48, 49, 45, 50, 48, 49, 50] 
0
